{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb9b05941-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3605"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3605"},"text":"§ 3605.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Transfer of jurisdiction over a probationer","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A court, after imposing a sentence, may transfer jurisdiction over a probationer or person on supervised release to the district court for any other district to which the person is required to proceed as a condition of his probation or release, or is permitted to proceed, with the concurrence of such court. A later transfer of jurisdiction may be made in the same manner. A court to which jurisdiction is transferred under this section is authorized to exercise all powers over the probationer or releasee that are permitted by this subchapter or subchapter B or D of chapter 227.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb9b2c942-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473/tII/s212/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–473, title II, § 212(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/2003"},"text":"98 Stat. 2003","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb9b2c943-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb9b2c944-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb9b2c945-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1987","children":[],"tail":", and applicable only to offenses committed after the taking effect of this section, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/473/s235/a/1"},"text":"section 235(a)(1) of Pub. L. 98–473","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s3551"},"text":"section 3551 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
